Here are the two files:

**`SortableList.razor`** — markup with `@typeparam TItem`, renders items in a `<ul>` with Move Up/Down buttons (disabled at boundaries).

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — `partial class` code-behind that:
- Copies `Items` into a private `_items` list in `OnParametersSet` (never mutates the input).
- Swaps elements on button click.
- Invokes `OnOrderChanged` with a read-only copy of the reordered list.

Usage matches your example — just note the template parameter is `ItemTemplate`:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = [ /* ... */ ];

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
